The paper deals with sub-Nyquist sampling of analog signals, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of Gabor frames and compressed sensing also suggests that the paper may belong to the subcategories of sparse signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the analysis of the proposed architecture in the presence of noise may also make the paper relevant to the subcategory of learning theory (cs.LG).
